{"id":"d=origam-topic-3952//p=c72a37b013aa49268276d6f1d939bcca","tags":{"__document_id":["origam-topic-3952"],"__file_type":["text/plain"],"__file_id":["f915e2bff7d74234a51ca32486b57b0a"],"__file_part":["32d3b29f0e5f468f8c9af561046eda4a"],"__part_n":["0"],"__sect_n":["0"],"source":["origam-community"],"category":["docs"],"categoryId":["8"],"topicId":["3952"],"url":["https://community.origam.com/t/how-to-create-screens/3952"],"title":["How to create Screens"]},"payload":{"url":"","schema":"20231218A","file":"content.txt","text":"# How to create Screens\n\nCategory: docs\nURL: https://community.origam.com/t/how-to-create-screens/3952\n\n@vikter (2025-02-14 11:06:41Z):\n   \n This guide will walk you through the process of creating user screens based on screen sections. \n A user screen in ORIGAM is composed of one or more screen sections, where each screen section serves as a separate \u201Ccontainer\u201D for displaying data from one or more different entities. \n For example, imagine a partner directory, where one section contains data about the partner (e.g., company name, address, etc.), and another section contains information about individual contact persons and their details (e.g., name, surname, phone, email, etc.). \n \n [!success]- Prerequisites for further work \n To follow along, you must meet the following five basic prerequisites: \n \n  Running database server  \n  Running ORIGAM Server  \n  Project created in ORIGAM Architect  \n  Entities and fields created  \n  Running client application in your browser  \n \n Once these prerequisites are set up, log into the client application using the  username and password you created  during the project setup. \n \n You can create screens using a wizard (action) or by manually setting them up. \n   Screen with Action \n To create a screen using a wizard, simply right-click on the entity in the Model Browser for which you want to create a screen, then select  Actions  /  Create Screen : \n          Create Screen action  448\u00D7658 18.8 KB         \n A wizard will then appear: \n          New Screen wizard #1  590\u00D7529 7.19 KB         \n To create a screen, the wizard will also need to create a screen section and a data structure for it. \n In the next step, name your screen and choose the fields you want to include. In addition to the fields you\u2019ve created, default fields that hold meta information (such as who created the record and when) are also included: \n          New Screen wizard #2  590\u00D7529 8.84 KB         \n In the next step, you will see a summary of what you are about to create: \n          New Screen wizard #3  590\u00D7529 6.59 KB         \n After clicking  Start , your new structures will be created: \n          New Screen wizard #4  590\u00D7529 6.6 KB         \n Click  Show Result  to navigate to the Model Browser under the  Find results  tab: \n   \n You can then click on any of the created items, which will take you to the Model Browser tree where the item is selected (for example, the newly created screen): \n          Screen in Model Browser tree  226\u00D7437 10.4 KB         \n Double-click on your new screen to view its details: \n          Screen details  936\u00D7505 26.1 KB         \n In this example, the screen contains just one screen section\u2014the one created by the wizard: \n          Screen with one Screen section  704\u00D7403 6.49 KB         \n What\u2019s important in the screen details are the  Data Source ,  Name , and the selection of all existing screen sections in the  Toolbox : \n          Screen details  210\u00D7355 6.52 KB         \n   Screen Section overview \n Let\u2019s take a closer look at the screen section the wizard created for us. \n Here, you can again see the  Data Source ,  Name , and the  Toolbox , which contains all the fields of the entity: \n          Screen Section details  834\u00D7445 12.1 KB         \n   Data Structure overview \n The last artifact created by the wizard is the data structure: \n          Data Structure for the Screen  276\u00D7341 7.35 KB         \n   Manual procedure \n Since screens are composed of screen sections, we need to create those first. \n   Screen Section creation \n In the Model Browser under  User Interface  /  Screen Sections , right-click on the package folder of your application and select  New  /  Screen Section : \n          New Screen Section  346\u00D7437 12.5 KB         \n In the screen section editor, you must first select the data source for your screen section\u2014choose the entity for which you want to create the screen: \n          Screen Section Data Source selection  566\u00D7360 13.1 KB         \n After selecting the data source entity, you will see all its fields in the Toolbox. You can then drag and drop the fields you want to display on your screen. \n Form field types will be automatically assigned based on the entity field types: \n          Form field creation  537\u00D7449 9.","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-04-29T00:23:31"},"vector":[0.010069683,-0.010511852,-0.072182134,-0.018987168,0.0041145873,-0.0026750998,-0.015245865,-0.025933571,0.0032311263,-0.017874636,0.04648491,0.01223043,-0.010278626,0.026600875,-0.032023914,-0.039158124,-0.012352998,0.008419713,0.06021031,-0.0024305687,-0.004757555,-0.025469048,0.039374456,0.024040986,0.035988487,0.057599638,0.010941635,-0.020616505,0.046604894,-0.028908558,-0.00018079266,-0.06740351,0.021493642,-0.019541197,0.0009070762,-0.017326558,-0.020138808,-0.0048803547,-0.039309695,-0.0014437131,-0.028087236,-0.0145670185,-0.01083627,0.010214451,-0.043400757,-0.048235938,0.032247163,0.00017383284,0.034868628,-0.057069752,-0.0316576,0.021874182,0.040895108,-0.028850013,0.037754975,0.06929006,-0.04629857,0.002085319,-0.0529053,0.029175414,-0.019814795,0.015253325,-0.025686206,-0.010654507,0.019721031,-0.0003803293,-0.028971262,0.0048433933,-0.032818526,-0.037544176,-0.02516041,0.04335069,-0.015